        <argsstring>(XUartPs *InstancePtr)</argsstring>
        <name>XUartPs_SelfTest</name>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="struct_x_uart_ps" kindref="compound">XUartPs</ref> *</type>
          <declname>InstancePtr</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>This function runs a self-test on the driver and hardware device. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This self test performs a local loopback and verifies data can be sent and received.</para><para>The time for this test is proportional to the baud rate that has been set prior to calling this function.</para><para>The mode and control registers are restored before return.</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is a pointer to the <ref refid="struct_x_uart_ps" kindref="compound">XUartPs</ref> instance</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_SUCCESS if the test was successful</para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_UART_TEST_FAIL if the test failed looping back the data</para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para><para><simplesect kind="note"><para></para></simplesect>
This function can hang if the hardware is not functioning properly. </para>        </detaileddescription>
